_json.gridTitle: Portable Ironing Table and summer sewing - Diary of a Quilter - a quilt blog
_json.description: I am feeling more productive than I thought I would this summer. It’s kind of a pleasant surprise. And it may not last all summer, but I’m taking it in snatches when I can. My goal is to make a dent in my never ending pile of WIP’s (Works In Progress). I’m even quilting a new project myself. It’s the one I started way back in March. I’m going to write a pattern for this one, so stay tuned. I’m also piecing my Family Tree quilt borders. I did the name stitching on a road trip last winter, ...
